<p><strong>6. <a href="https://www.bbb.org">Better Business Bureau (BBB)</a>. DA 91, Trust Signal</strong></p>
<p>The BBB has a DA of 91 and carries a unique trust signal that no other directory provides. An accredited BBB listing tells Google and consumers that your business meets ethical standards. BBB profiles include a dofollow backlink to your website.</p>
<p>Membership costs $500+ per year depending on your location and business size. That price tag keeps many competitors from listing. The dofollow link from a DA 91 domain, combined with the trust signal, makes BBB one of the highest-value paid local citation sites available. BBB accreditation also appears in Google Knowledge Panels.</p>
<p><strong>7. <a href="https://foursquare.com">Foursquare</a>. Powers 100+ Apps</strong></p>
<p>Foursquare has a DA of 92 and functions primarily as a data aggregator. Your Foursquare business data feeds into Uber, Airbnb, Twitter, Snapchat, Samsung, and over 100 other apps and platforms.</p>
<p>Claiming your Foursquare listing is free. Links are nofollow. The real value is data distribution. When you update your business information on Foursquare, that data propagates across its partner network. One listing effectively creates presence on dozens of platforms. For businesses that depend on mobile discovery, Foursquare is non-negotiable.</p>
<p><strong>8. <a href="https://www.yellowpages.com">Yellow Pages (YP)</a>. DA 82, DoFollow Links</strong></p>
<p>Yellow Pages has a DA of 82 and provides dofollow backlinks from your business listing page. The platform still attracts millions of monthly visitors, primarily from older demographics and Google search referrals.</p>
<p>Free listings include your business name, address, phone, hours, and website link. The dofollow link makes YP one of the most valuable free citation sites for direct <a href="/glossary/link-building/">link building</a> value. Paid upgrades add enhanced profiles, photos, and priority placement. For the free listing alone, YP delivers a strong backlink at zero cost.</p>
<p><strong>9. <a href="https://www.linkedin.com">LinkedIn Company Page</a>. DA 99</strong></p>
<p>LinkedIn has a DA of 99, making it the second-highest authority platform on this list behind Google. Your LinkedIn Company Page includes your business address, website, and description.</p>
<p>Links are nofollow. The value for <a href="/blog/seo-for-b2b/">B2B companies</a> is enormous. LinkedIn pages rank in Google for branded searches. Google uses LinkedIn data to validate business entities. A complete Company Page with employee connections, regular posts, and a verified website URL strengthens your brand entity signals across search engines.</p>
<p><strong>10. <a href="https://nextdoor.com">Nextdoor</a>. DA 83, Hyper-Local</strong></p>
<p>Nextdoor has a DA of 83 and reaches over 90 million verified users across 300,000+ neighborhoods. It is the only social platform that verifies users by physical address.</p>
<p>Business pages are free. Links are nofollow. <a href="/blog/nextdoor-for-business/">Nextdoor recommendations</a> carry weight because they come from verified neighbors. Google indexes Nextdoor business pages. Home services, restaurants, and retail businesses get the strongest results from Nextdoor because purchasing decisions in these categories depend heavily on local trust.</p>
<p><strong>11. <a href="https://www.manta.com">Manta</a>. DA 74, Free DoFollow Links</strong></p>
<p>Manta has a DA of 74 and specializes in small business profiles. Free listings include a dofollow backlink to your website, your business description, hours, and contact information.</p>
<p>Manta profiles rank in Google for "[business name] + [city]" queries. The dofollow link from a DA 74 domain costs nothing. Profile completion takes about 10 minutes. Manta attracts less traffic than Yelp or YP, but the free dofollow link makes it worth the small time investment for any <a href="/blog/local-seo-guide/">local SEO strategy</a>.</p>
