<p><strong>18. <a href="https://www.superpages.com">Superpages</a>. DA 72, Free DoFollow</strong></p>
<p>Superpages has a DA of 72 and provides free dofollow backlinks from business listings. The platform covers all industries and accepts free submissions.</p>
<p>Listing creation takes under 10 minutes. Your profile includes business name, address, phone, hours, and a website link with a dofollow attribute. Superpages profiles get indexed by Google. The free dofollow link from a DA 72 domain is valuable for businesses building their <a href="/glossary/citation/">local citation</a> foundation.</p>
<p><strong>19. <a href="https://www.thumbtack.com">Thumbtack</a>. DA 78, Service Providers</strong></p>
<p>Thumbtack has a DA of 78 and connects service providers with local customers. The platform covers 1,000+ service categories from photography to plumbing to personal training.</p>
<p>Profiles are free to create. Thumbtack uses a pay-per-lead model for connecting with customers. Links are nofollow. The platform's strength is lead generation, not direct backlink value. For <a href="/blog/seo-for-service-businesses/">service businesses</a> that want both visibility and customer acquisition, Thumbtack serves double duty as a citation and a lead source.</p>
<p><strong>20. <a href="https://www.trustpilot.com">Trustpilot</a>. DA 93, Review Authority</strong></p>
<p>Trustpilot has a DA of 93 and hosts 320 million+ reviews across every industry. Your business profile includes a website link and displays your aggregate star rating.</p>
<p>Links are nofollow. The SEO value comes from Trustpilot review snippets appearing in Google search results for your brand name. A strong Trustpilot rating improves click-through rates on branded searches. Google treats Trustpilot as a trusted review source. Free listings are available. Paid plans add review invitation tools and analytics.</p>
<p><strong>21. <a href="https://www.data-axle.com">Data Axle</a>. Powers 100+ Directories</strong></p>
<p>Data Axle (formerly Infogroup) is a data aggregator, not a traditional directory. Your business data submitted to Data Axle flows into 100+ websites, apps, and directories automatically.</p>
<p>This is paid. The cost varies by business size and data volume. The value is scale. Instead of manually submitting to 100 individual directories, one Data Axle submission populates them all. Data Axle feeds major platforms including 411.com, Superpages, and dozens of local directories. For businesses with <a href="/blog/multi-location-seo/">multiple locations</a>, Data Axle saves hundreds of hours.</p>
<p><strong>22. <a href="https://www.neustarlocaleze.biz">Neustar Localeze</a>. Voice Search</strong></p>
<p>Neustar Localeze (now part of TransUnion) is a data aggregator that specializes in powering voice search results. Your business data submitted to Neustar feeds into 80+ platforms, including Alexa, Siri responses, and navigation systems.</p>
<p>This is paid. The voice search angle is critical. When someone asks Alexa "find a plumber near me," the results often come from Neustar's data. For businesses that depend on <a href="/blog/voice-search-seo/">voice search visibility</a>, Neustar Localeze is the aggregator that matters most.</p>
<p><strong>23. <a href="https://patch.com">Patch</a>. DA 78, Community News</strong></p>
<p>Patch has a DA of 78 and operates as a hyper-local community news and events platform across 1,200+ US communities. Business listings on Patch appear alongside local news content.</p>
<p>Free listings include your business details and a website link. Patch pages rank well in Google for local queries because the platform publishes fresh content daily. The community context gives your listing more topical relevance than a generic directory. Best for businesses that want <a href="/blog/local-content-marketing/">local content</a> association.</p>
<p><strong>24. <a href="https://www.alignable.com">Alignable</a>. DA 60, Local Networking</strong></p>
<p>Alignable has a DA of 60 and functions as a local business networking platform. Think LinkedIn but focused on small business owners connecting within their geographic area.</p>
<p>Free profiles include your business information, services, and website link. Alignable's referral system lets other business owners recommend you. Those recommendations show up on your profile and add social proof. Best for <a href="/blog/build-online-presence-local-business/">service businesses</a> that get clients through referrals.</p>
<p><strong>25. Local Chamber of Commerce. DoFollow, Hyper-Local</strong></p>
<p>Your local Chamber of Commerce is not a single website. It is whatever chamber serves your city or county. Chamber directories typically have DA 30-60 with dofollow backlinks.</p>
<p>Membership costs $200-$1,000+ per year. The dofollow link from a hyper-local, trusted domain carries significant weight for <a href="/blog/local-seo-ranking-factors/">local SEO ranking factors</a>. Google associates chamber membership with business legitimacy. Chamber listings also create a geographically relevant citation that reinforces your service area. Check your local chamber's directory before joining to verify the link is dofollow.</p>
